---
title: Curried Chicken Salad Wraps with Golden Raisins & Shredded Carrots
description: This lunch is (quite literally) gold! A mix of sour cream, mayo, and curry spices coat chicken and golden raisins in creamy, golden-hued flavor. The chicken salad is then stuffed inside steamy tortillas and topped with shredded carrots for even more crunch and color. Glorious texture, rich flavors, brilliant hues—yep, that’s a solid (gold) wrap!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/curried-chicken-salad-wraps-f2916b4a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/curried-chicken-salad-wraps-62b201f72d3c96889305dce2-4c4a281d.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 60 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1100 mg
time required: 10 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/curried-chicken-salad-wraps-62b201f72d3c96889305dce2
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve @lemon{1}. Finely dice @fully cooked chicken breasts{9%ounce}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @golden raisins{1%ounce}, scallion whites, and juice from half the lemon.

In a second medium bowl, toss @shredded carrots{4%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

To bowl with raisin mixture, add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @curry powder{1.25%teaspoon}, and @sugar{0.5%teaspoon}; stir to combine. Stir in chicken and scallion greens. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add more curry powder if you like a stronger flavor!

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Spread chicken salad on the bottom third of each tortilla, leaving a 1-inch border on both sides. Top with as many carrots as you like. Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal; divide between plates. Serve with any remaining carrots on the side.